comments.text: As an Algerian, I love Zidane because he is of Algerian origin, and as a football fan and amateur who was not destined to become a professional in a country like Algeria. His punch to Materazzi really made me cry, as I supported the French national team, even though we in Algeria have some grudges buried deep inside us because of their occupation and colonization of us and their killing of our ancestors. Despite all of this, Zidane removed those grudges, made me support France with all my heart, and also because of him I fell in love with this game. The difference now is not big in comparing Zidane to Maradona and Pele.
